Dapo Abiodun, the Ogun State Governor, will on Thursday in­augurate an Elders’ Advisory Council at the Obas’ Complex inside the State Secretariat in Abeokuta by 2pm. The Governor said the com­position of the Council was part of the government’s desire to tap from the foun­tain of wisdom of the elder­ly in our society and to give the state the benefit of the knowledge garnered over the years by these statesmen and women. “It is in order to walk the talk about our commitment to inclusive and participatory governance that we are doing this. We stand to benefit from these elders in our midst”, a statement issued by Abidoun spokesman, Kunle Somorin said. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The newly constituted Governors’ Elders Advisory Council (GEAC) comprises of critical stakeholders in the All Progressives Congress (APC) and outside the main political parties in the State.